        "title": "Charnwood Eco Hub Makerspace",
        "excerpt":"Help us make a makerspace!      We‚Äôre excited to announce that our new makerspace is coming together ‚Äî a place where creativity, craftsmanship, and community meet. To make it happen, we‚Äôre looking for skilled and enthusiastic people who can help us set things up and get everything running smoothly.   If you‚Äôve got experience in woodworking, metalworking, electronics, workshop setup, or just a knack for problem-solving, we‚Äôd love to hear from you!   Here‚Äôs what we already have in the workshop:      Laser Cutter   Vacuum Former   Industrial Sewing Machine &amp; Overlocker   Vinyl cutter   Pillar Drill   Lathe   CNC Router   Table Saw   3D printers   Electric planer   A growing set of hand tools   And here‚Äôs what‚Äôs on the way:      Bench saw   Band Saw   Belt Sander   Knitting machine   Soldering Stations   More specialist tools and equipment as we expand   We‚Äôre building more than just a workshop ‚Äî we‚Äôre building a community resource. By volunteering your time and skills now, you‚Äôll be helping lay the foundations for a space where people can learn, share, and make amazing things together.   üëâ Interested? Drop us a message at charnwoodecohub@gmail.com.   Let‚Äôs create something incredible ‚Äî together.   ","categories": [],
